description:

Review FROM REVSPINES:

Big rubber. It's not perfect in one thing but it' s good in every way. Both in Topspin and block / crush. It does not produce the same amount of spin as t 05 but very spinning. On the other hand it is much easier to handle turns in, to block or crush. Control is very good for Off rubber.

As its official description says, T80 has the perfect balance between Tenergy in terms of speed and lap. The touch is also amazing, good precision and has a good throwing angle.

Tenergy 80 is an offensive rubber complete with good turn and speed. I tried this on my backhand and felt the rubber was great for short snaps and drives and great for blocking. Although the sensitivity is low enough to turn in, it itself is able to produce many rounds on encouragement and especially service. It plays best in medium distance and away from table whether blocking or fighting looping. Pushing close to the table will require adjustment due to Spring Sponge tendency to remove the ball (though many backspin is generated). The main limitations I found with this rubber were power loops on the backhand side hard to run near the table because sponge springs but works well away from the table.
